  m_Name: Frieder Butzmann - Wolfsburg_Vinyl
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::RecordData
  title: Wolfsburg
  author: Frieder Butzmann
  album: Das Maedchen Auf Der Schaukel
  year: 1984
  description: "Frieder Butzmann studied the communication science foundations of
    language and music, as well as musicology and psychology, at the Technical University
    of Berlin from 1975 to 1982. He was a member of various bands (including Nachdenkliche
    Wehrpflichtigen with Diedrich Diederichsen and FM Einheit), helped establish
    Burkhardt Seiler\u2019s record label Zensor, and worked on the restoration and
    acoustic documentation of analog synthesizers and effects units at the Studio
    for Electro-Instrumental Music (STEIM) in Amsterdam. Since 1979, he has worked
    as a freelance composer, radio playwright, actor, artist, lecturer, and sound
    designer. "
